com.atakmap.android.http.rest

Class NetworkOperationManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.android.http.rest.NetworkOperationManager

  • public class NetworkOperationManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Allows components & plugins to leverage the HTTPRequestService to perform asynchronous operations (including but not limited to HTTP, FTP, etc network operations). Request types should be registered with this class. ATAK Core tools can use Parcelable to pass data to/from its Operation instances. See Mission Package Tool for sample code. Due to plugin class loading constraints, plugins should use something like JSON to to pass data to/from its Operation instances. See Enterprise Sync Plugin for sample code. Both tools and plugins can receive callbacks upon completion. Use HTTPRequestManager to initiate operations.

      • register

        public static java.lang.Integer register(java.lang.String clazz,
                                         Operation handler)
        Register handler, return unique requestType. Registering a handler instance may help when class names/paths are mangled by proguard and may provide a slight performance bump for not recreating operations for each request This uses an empty salt when generating the identifier which could end up duplicate identifiers
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to register
        handler - the operation handler
        Returns:
        returns a unique rest type identifier as an integer

      • register

        public static java.lang.Integer register(java.lang.String clazz,
                                         Operation handler,
                                         java.lang.String salt)
        Register handler, return unique requestType. Optionally salt the clazz hash. e.g. this could be used to allow a single Operation implementation to be used for multiple request types
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to register
        handler - the operation handler
        salt - the salt to be used to generate a unique id

        returns a unique rest type identifier as an integer
